    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Pieter Nanninck to Miklós Oláh (Leuven, 12 May 1538)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. He has finished with the Demosthenes translation and
                            found the courage because he knows not only the erudition but also the
                            benevolence of his patron, Oláh. So far only Melanchthon has attempted
                            to translate Demosthenes, but it was not a very successful translation,
                            and since then only one nerd has tried to amend Melanchthon’s
                            translation. Nanninck has followed the punctuation, colons and divisions
                            more conservatively, he is asking Oláh to help him before he publishes
                            it. 2. He hears that the Emperor is coming here with his brother; he
                            asks Oláh to be present as well, or at least he should write through
                            Damião de Góis what he should change in the prolog. He also asks him to
                            help the bearer of the letter, the prior of Tehenburch; they have namely
                            tried to oust him from his lawful estate. 3. After he wrote this letter,
                            Damião de Góis returned with his previous letter, so he is sending it
                            again.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/55A7D581-2368-4887-9167-624264A64D45
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">
                    <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Deditissimus cliens Petrus Nannius Nicolao
                        Olaho.</add>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] En rursus alteram epistolam, cum enim solvendo sim, hoc est:
                    absolverim meam tibi in <persName>Demosthene</persName> promissam translationem,
                    abiit pudor, vel potius δυσωπία,<note xml:id="note.1">‘coyness’.</note>
                    successit audacia. Novi enim, <choice>
                        <orig>quam</orig>
                        <supplied>quem</supplied>
                    </choice> habeo patronum non solum litteratum, sed et clementem et indulgentem.
                    Spero, postquam accesserit titulus tui amplissimi nominis, librum omnino non
                    plausibilem, sed etiam aliqua aeternitate diuturnam fore. Solus
                        <persName>Melanchton</persName> cum uno et altero aliquid in Demosthene
                        tentavit,<note xml:id="note.2"><hi rend="italic">Contra Aristogitonem
                            Demosthenis Orationes duae doctissimae, à Philippo Melanchthone iam
                            primum latinitate donatae</hi>, Haganoae, 1527.</note> verum adeo
                    plerisque non satisfacit, ut nuper quidam sciolus eadem denuo verterit, sed
                    infinitis partibus infra dignitatem eius, quem aemulabatur, vel potius corrigere
                    studebat. Melanchtonis interpretatio liberior est, saepe enim paraphrasten
                    sapit. Nos religiosiores sumus, servata enim sententia etiam commatum, colon et
                    periodon cum numeris ipsis ferme speciem servavimus. Utinam adesses et tuam
                    acutisssimam prudentiam consulerem, antequam exiret in publicum. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] Audio <persName>caesarem</persName> huc venturum cum
                        <persName>fratre</persName>;<note xml:id="note.3">King Ferdinand I.</note>
                    quaeso te per omnia sacra Musarum, habeamus te tunc praesentem, vel per hunc vel
                        <persName>Damianum</persName><note xml:id="note.4">Damião de Góis.</note>
                    mihi rescribe, quid in prologo mutatum velis. Quia magnus habeor apud meum
                    <milestone unit="pb" facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/24917A2E-4089-4968-8422-2D3761B6F386
                        "/>Holaum<note xml:id="note.5">I.e. Olahum.</note>
                    maximum, multi mihi invident, multi quoque multa a me petunt, quod per te
                    sperant confici posse. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Multos reieci, <persName>hunc</persName>,<note xml:id="note.6">We do
                        not know the name of the Prior at Tehenburch.</note> qui has meas litteras
                    ad te defert, reiicere non potui, nec debui; est enim vir non minus probus, quam
                    litteratus et summa mecum amicitia coniunctus causam apud caesarem hanc debet.
                    Est coenobium quoddam in <placeName>Tehenburch</placeName>, comes eius loci,
                    homo, qui nonnisi septem aut octo pagos habet in tota ditione, hanc legem
                    monachis iniunxit, ne quempiam deinceps reciperent, ne priorem suum mutarent ac
                    observatum est <choice>
                        <orig>utrinque</orig>
                        <supplied>utrumque</supplied>
                    </choice> ad amussim. Postea hic prior eligitur a toto ordine in generalem, ac
                    ideo necessario abiit. Hinc causam spoliandi coepit tyrannus, quasi leges suae
                    violatae essent, ac omnia bona tam ecclesiastica, quam secularia <choice>
                        <orig>consiscunt</orig>
                        <supplied>confiscunt</supplied>
                    </choice>. Ipsi contra eum cupiunt agere, non ut contra Lutheranum, sed ut
                    contra iniustum invasorem. <choice>
                        <orig>Hi quod propter</orig>
                        <supplied>Hinc si praeter</supplied>
                    </choice> ullam molestiam operam et consilio possis eum iuvare, valde cuperem,
                    sin minus, nolim te vel minimum, vel mea, vel meorum causa vexare. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.5"><placeName>Lovani</placeName> quarto Idus Maias. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.6">[3.] Litteris scriptis rediit <persName>Damianus a Goes</persName>,
                    qui te <placeName>Antverpiae</placeName> non invenit, quare et litteras<note
                        xml:id="note.7">Ep. 601.<ref>olahus.tei.15380506_1</ref></note> per illum ad
                    te missas, eas per eundem monachum virum doctum et probum, de quo supra memini,
                    ad te remitto. Iterum vale, Optime et Eruditissime Patrone. </p>
            </div>
        </body>
